# Founder OS - your gitignore.
# Installed over the shipped developer .gitignore at the moment version history
# becomes yours (setup with git present, or "own my history" later).
#
# The difference matters: the developer gitignore protects the PUBLIC repo by
# ignoring founder data. This one protects YOU by tracking it. Your identity,
# priorities, decisions, brain log, clients - all of it goes into your local
# history, so "full version history" means your data too, not just the engine.
# Only secrets, runtime state, and per-machine files stay out.

# Secrets. Never tracked, never committed. The connect skill writes keys here
# and nowhere else.
.env
.env.*
*.key

# Private-name guard patterns. Your names power the pre-commit guard but never
# enter history, so they can never leave this machine even if you ever push.
scripts/private-name-patterns.txt

# Runtime state. Session snapshots, change logs, update staging and backups.
# Regenerated constantly; history would be noise.
state/
brain/.snapshot.md

# Connector and voice runtime. Machine-specific; the connect and add-voice
# skills regenerate these. Secrets live in .env, not here.
connectors/
voice/

# Per-machine Claude settings. Local overrides stay local.
CLAUDE.local.md
AGENTS.local.md
GEMINI.local.md
.mcp.local.json
.claude/settings.local.json

# Caches and editor noise.
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.obsidian/
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
